Judge Gorsuch will do just that, and I look forward to a fair and timely confirmation process by the Senate.

I was proud to vote today in support of H. J. Res. 43. This is a disapproval of one of President Obama's rules that threatens to deprive states of Title X (low-income family planning) grant money if they do not comply with the Obama rule and fund Planned Parenthood. H.J. Res 43 would repeal the Obama Administration’s rule, allowing states the freedom to distribute Title X grant money in a way that serves the needs of their constituents.

Later this afternoon, the House of Representatives will vote on my friend, U.S. Representative Bradley Byrne's bill, H.J.Res. 83. This bill will turn back one of the Obama Administration's OSHA rules which punished businesses for violations in the far past, though the law on the books states businesses can only be punished for violations in the past 6 months. This power grab did nothing to protect workers, and I heard time and time again from constituents that it only increased regulatory red tape for small businesses in #AL03.

Jeff Sessions is a man of the highest integrity, and his allegiance to the law and truth is undeniable. Democrats should be spending their time heeding President Trump's call to put America first and joining Republicans in addressing the many problems facing its nation, like constructing the border wall, repealing Obamacare, and rebuilding our military.

Today, with my support, the House of Representatives will vote on HR 1181, the Veterans 2nd Amendment Protection Act and HR 1259, the VA Accountability First Act. HR 1181 ensures that veterans are given due process and that a judicial authority must make a determination if an individual's information should be shared with the National Criminal Background System, not a VA bureaucrat. HR 1259 gives the VA Secretary increased flexibility to remove, demote, or suspend any VA employee for performance or misconduct, while still protecting whistleblowers.

Israel is one of our most important allies and we are dedicated to its security and freedom.  As a Christian, Israel is sacred to me as it is to many other Americans.  I congratulate President Trump on his efforts recognizing Jerusalem as the capital of Israel. As past presidents have used words on this subject, President Trump uses actions.

I am pleased S. 1266, the Enhancing Veteran Care Act, passed the House this week with my strong support.  This bill should help ensure our brave men and women who have served in uniform get the best possible care we can provide them.  The legislation allows the VA to contract with non-profits during investigations which should help speed up the process.  I will continue to support common-sense bills like this that hold our VA accountable. #Veterans

As a strong supporter of our Second Amendment rights, I was proud to support the Concealed Carry Reciprocity Act.  This common-sense legislation will allow any law-abiding gun owners to concealed carry across state lines without penalty.  I am pleased this bill passed the House today.
